race.comment: NOVEL APPROACH (4) turned in an eye-catching run last time when kept coming to finish second at Benalla. Expected to measure up over this journey and rates a leading chance to break through. PLEASE ME DO (5) was also doing her best work late last start to grab third at Bendigo. Doesn't have to improve much off that to go close. ETERNITY STAR (1) has only been thereabouts of late but strips fitter fourth-up and finds a suitable assignment. Can play a role. UPINTHECITY (6) finds it tough to break through but was doing her best work late last start on the Wagga Riverside surface, closing off nicely into a midfield finish. Will appreciate the added trip and could cause them a scare if they overdo it in front. BLACK FROST (7) is a Frosted gelding on debut from the Weeding camp. Keeping safe.
